<bioghist encodinganalog="545"><head>History of the Xavier University Futures Committee</head><p>On December 5, 1988, the president of Xavier University, Albert J. DiUlio, S.J., established a committee which he named the "Futures Committee." Its task, as the president explained, was "to articulate a direction, set priorities and develop a plan for implementing these for Xavier between now and the year 2000." The Futures Committee completed its work and submitted its final report to DiUlio's successor, James. E. Hoff, S.J., in the spring of 1991. The final report was published and distributed to the Xavier community in July, 1991. Although self-described as a standing committee, it went out of existence upon the completion of its task.</p><bioghist><p>Not specified</p></bioghist></bioghist><scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a"><head>Scope and Content</head><p>Records resulting from the activities of the Xavier University Futures Committee. Records include meeting minutes, reports, surveys, letters, memos and related documents.</p><scopecontent><p>Not specified</p></scopecontent></scopecontent><arrangement encodinganalog="351$b"><head>Statement of Arrangement</head><p>Meeting minutes and related materials are arranged chronologically into folders. Committee documents (including the final report) are arranged following the meeting minutes and are also arranged chronologically.</p></arrangement><accessrestrict encodinganalog="506"><head>Restrictions on Access</head><p>Restricted access. Please contact the Xavier University Archives staff.</p></accessrestrict><prefercite encodinganalog="524"><head>Preferred Citation</head><p>Box Number, Folder Number, XUA-15, Futures Committee records, Special Collections and Archives, Xavier University Library, Cincinnati, Ohio.</p></prefercite><controlaccess><head>Indexing Terms</head><p>The following terms have been used to index the description of this collection in the library's online public access catalog.</p><controlaccess><head>S